b'Fun Facts about Emus:
- A group of emus is called a \xe2\x80\x9cmob.\xe2\x80\x9d
- Emus can run up to 30 miles an hour.
- Males incubate the eggs and care for the chicks.
- One emu egg can feed 4-6 adults. 
- Emu eggs are about the size of an avocado.
- Emu eggs are sooo pretty!

b'Pro-Grow Tip from our neighbor Amanda at @ajwildwayfarm: 
\xe2\x80\x9cGet your hands dirty. Soak up the sunshine. Grow something. 2021 coming in hot. Want to know how easy it is to save pepper seeds? 
- Pop them out of the pepper. 
- Put them on a dry surface (I\xe2\x80\x99m going to use an old paper bag). 
- Ditch the damaged ones. 
- Flick them over in a day or two so they dry evenly. 
- That\xe2\x80\x99s. It.\xe2\x80\x9d'

b'Facts about hummingbirds:
- The average weight of a hummingbird is less than a nickel.
- A group of hummingbirds is called a \xe2\x80\x9ccharm.\xe2\x80\x9d
- They can consume up to double their body weight in a day.
- A hummingbird\xe2\x80\x99s heart beats over 1,200 times per minute.
- People always get excited when they spot a hummingbird.
